    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="269"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–1653: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-16T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 16, 1953—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 7. Re Turkish candidacy for <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName>Katz Suchy</persName> (Poland) and <persName>Nosek</persName>
                            (Czechoslovakia) informed <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> officer
                            that Poland will be Soviet-bloc candidate to succeed Greece on <gloss
                                target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName>Ardalan</persName> (Iran) stated that Iran will vote for
                            Turkey.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName>Ludin</persName> (Afghanistan) stated that Afghanistan will
                            vote for Turkey. <persName>Ludin</persName> added as personal
                            recommendation that he believes Arab support of Turkish candidacy would
                            be furthered by direct and high-level Turkish approaches in the Arab
                            capitals. He also expected that Arab support for Turkey could be
                            beneficially influenced by expressions of Turkish sympathy as regards
                            colonial questions.</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_ENGENH1">Engen</persName> (Norway) said that as
                            his instructions now stand Norway will vote for Poland. On personal
                            basis he suggested that votes of Norway, Denmark and other western
                            European powers could be beneficially influenced by high-level US
                            approach in western European capitals, urging that <gloss
                                target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> powers make common cause in support
                            of Turkish partner and that Turkey’s election to eastern European <gloss
                                target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> seat is in direct interest of <gloss
                                target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> powers.<note n="1" xml:id="d269fn1"
                                >Marginal notation beside last paragraph: “Note!”</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
